<node id="World Health Organization">
  <data key="d0">World Health Organization</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The World Health Organization is a specialized agency of the United Nations responsible for international public health and overseeing global health initiatives.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization (WHO) is an international public health agency that estimates and addresses global health issues, including diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization is a global health authority involved in various health initiatives, including diabetes prevention and management.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Health Organization is a global health agency involved in diabetes research, prevention, and control initiatives.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5384df975133ef2a52113cd3ca0f897e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57782c3301473bc8e8dafd9683ab2650&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-942e000d0de99e8628ab9c8bcbe83419&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b253411e54c35aa95f5f9179723bba3b</data>
