<node id="Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus">
  <data key="d0">Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus is a prevalent form of diabetes characterized primarily by insulin resistance. This condition is increasingly diagnosed at younger ages, particularly in developing countries, where it is often linked to lifestyle factors such as obesity and poor dietary habits. 

The disorder arises from defects in insulin secretion and is commonly associated with insulin resistance. As a metabolic disorder, its prevalence has notably increased among children, primarily attributed to the rise in childhood obesity. Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus necessitates management strategies that often include lifestyle changes, such as diet modification and increased physical activity, and may require medication to control the condition effectively.

The progression and severity of Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus can vary widely among individuals, influenced by genetic and environmental factors. Consequently, a comprehensive approach to management is crucial to mitigate the risks associated with this increasingly common health issue.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5384df975133ef2a52113cd3ca0f897e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8c827cc2249067692290d6a8a0e8018&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85ef35aaa38ac4f0c032c8bc3f6df559&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1400e1158e4f7be2283a0366ebf4f2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Children and Adolescents">
  <data key="d0">Children and Adolescents</data>
  <data key="d1">populationgroup</data>
  <data key="d2">Children and adolescents represent a demographic group that has recently shown an increasing prevalence of type 2 diabetes, often linked to rising childhood obesity rates.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fasting Plasma Glucose Concentration">
  <data key="d0">Fasting Plasma Glucose Concentration</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Fasting plasma glucose concentration is a critical measurement used to assess IFG and IGT, with specific values indicating the presence of these conditions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Oral Glucose Tolerance Test">
  <data key="d0">Oral Glucose Tolerance Test</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Oral Glucose Tolerance Test (OGTT) is a diagnostic method used to assess glucose metabolism and identify conditions such as IGT and diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;The Oral Glucose Tolerance Test (OGTT) is a definitive confirmatory diagnostic test for diabetes mellitus, assessing glucose levels after a glucose load.&lt;SEP&gt;An oral glucose tolerance test is used to assess blood glucose management and diagnose diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25fb88c8ed14936954356d104de095d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5c3e866099ac4f8457930aab67cc3bd0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769582109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Metabolic Syndrome">
  <data key="d0">Metabolic Syndrome</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Metabolic syndrome refers to a cluster of conditions often found in individuals with abnormal glucose tolerance, increasing the risk of cardiovascular disease.&lt;SEP&gt;Metabolic syndrome refers to a cluster of conditions that increase the risk of heart disease, stroke, and diabetes, often associated with IGT.&lt;SEP&gt;Metabolic syndrome is a cluster of conditions that increase the risk of heart disease, stroke, and diabetes, often characterized by specific diagnostic criteria.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Poly-Unsaturated Fatty Acids">
  <data key="d0">Poly-Unsaturated Fatty Acids</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Poly-unsaturated fatty acids are a type of fat that can lower plasma total and LDL cholesterol levels, beneficial for health.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mono-Unsaturated Fatty Acids">
  <data key="d0">Mono-Unsaturated Fatty Acids</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Mono-unsaturated fatty acids are a type of fat that contributes to lower plasma total and LDL cholesterol levels compared to poly-unsaturated fats.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Trans-Fatty Acids">
  <data key="d0">Trans-Fatty Acids</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Trans-fatty acids are harmful fats that raise plasma LDL cholesterol and lower HDL cholesterol, and should be minimized in the diet.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Insulin">
  <data key="d0">Insulin</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Insulin is a hormone used in pharmacological therapy for managing blood sugar levels in diabetes patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin is a hormone used in various formulations with differing action times for managing blood glucose levels in patients with diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin is a hormone used in medical treatment to control blood glucose levels in diabetic patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin is a hormone used in diabetes management to control blood glucose levels and is administered through various preparations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Metformin">
  <data key="d0">Metformin</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Metformin is an oral medication used as an insulin sensitizer to improve insulin sensitivity and decrease hepatic glucose production.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Exercise">
  <data key="d0">Exercise</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Exercise is crucial for managing diabetes by regulating blood glucose levels, aiding weight control, and improving insulin response.&lt;SEP&gt;Exercise involves physical activity that promotes health and weight management, recommended as part of a healthy lifestyle in managing dyslipidaemia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Weight Loss">
  <data key="d0">Weight Loss</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Weight loss is an important therapeutic goal for managing obesity and improving insulin resistance in individuals with type 2 diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Weight Loss refers to the reduction of body weight, often through dietary changes and increased physical activity, recommended for managing dyslipidaemia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Guidelines for Diabetes Care">
  <data key="d0">Guidelines for Diabetes Care</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The guidelines provide recommendations for the prevention, management, and care of individuals diagnosed with diabetes mellitus.&lt;SEP&gt;The guidelines provide recommendations and standards for the prevention, management, and care of diabetes mellitus.&lt;SEP&gt;Guidelines for diabetes care emphasize individualized nutrition therapy, management plans, and regular exercise for effective diabetes management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5fc5e661d0f94cc23c0188b9bbe4e08&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25fb88c8ed14936954356d104de095d4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cholesterol">
  <data key="d0">Cholesterol</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Cholesterol is a type of fat found in the blood, with levels affected by different types of fatty acids in the diet, important for health.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Body Mass Index">
  <data key="d0">Body Mass Index</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Body mass index (BMI) is a measurement that assesses body weight relative to height, used to classify individuals as underweight, normal weight, overweight, or obese.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Type 2 Diabetes">
  <data key="d0">Type 2 Diabetes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Type 2 diabetes is a chronic condition characterized by high blood sugar levels and various complications, with a significant number of cases remaining undiagnosed.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 diabetes is characterized by insulin resistance and is often associated with lifestyle factors.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 Diabetes is a chronic condition that affects the body's ability to metabolize sugar, and its management involves lifestyle changes and healthcare intervention.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Da Quing Study">
  <data key="d0">Da Quing Study</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The Da Quing Study is a research study from China that demonstrated the effectiveness of diet and exercise in reducing the risk of diabetes mellitus.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
