  <data key="d0">Tuomilehto et al.</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Tuomilehto et al. conducted research in Finland focusing on the incidence of diabetes in individuals at risk, highlighting the benefits of lifestyle modifications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Diabetes Prevention Programme Research Group">
  <data key="d0">Diabetes Prevention Programme Research Group</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Diabetes Prevention Programme Research Group conducted a study assessing the impact of lifestyle modifications and metformin on preventing Type 2 diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Community-based Healthy Lifestyle Programmes">
  <data key="d0">Community-based Healthy Lifestyle Programmes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Community-based Healthy Lifestyle Programmes are initiatives aimed at promoting healthy behaviors to prevent diabetes and other noncommunicable diseases.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578513</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="United Kingdom Prospective Diabetes Study Group">
  <data key="d0">United Kingdom Prospective Diabetes Study Group</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The United Kingdom Prospective Diabetes Study Group conducted research that demonstrated the importance of glucose control in reducing diabetic complications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578513</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Diabetes Control and Complications Trial">
  <data key="d0">Diabetes Control and Complications Trial</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The Diabetes Control and Complications Trial is a major clinical study assessing diabetes management strategies and outcomes.&lt;SEP&gt;The Diabetes Control and Complications Trial was a study in the USA that provided evidence on the benefits of tight blood glucose control in type 1 diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578513</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Diabetes Mellitus">
  <data key="d0">Diabetes Mellitus</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Diabetes Mellitus is a chronic health condition characterized by high blood sugar levels, which stems from the body's inability to produce or properly respond to insulin. This metabolic disorder manifests in a group of diseases, primarily classified into two main types: type 1 diabetes, which requires insulin for survival, and type 2 diabetes, which may or may not necessitate insulin for effective metabolic control. 

The prevalence of Diabetes Mellitus poses significant public health challenges globally, with an increasing incidence reported in various regions, including the Eastern Mediterranean. This condition affects individuals' quality of life by leading to serious complications, such as cardiovascular disease, kidney damage, and other health issues if not managed properly. The management of Diabetes Mellitus involves careful regulation of blood glucose levels as well as monitoring other factors such as blood pressure and lipid levels through diet, exercise, and potentially medication.

Diabetes Mellitus encompasses high blood sugar levels persisting over extended periods, which can be identified through various testing methods. It is critical to emphasize that Diabetes Mellitus affects how the body processes blood sugar, and thus, effective management is essential to prevent severe complications associated with this disorder. The significant rise in cases of Diabetes Mellitus highlights the need for increased awareness and proactive healthcare measures across affected populations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56d9ff3515afac60e7566e41837249a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5384df975133ef2a52113cd3ca0f897e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8c827cc2249067692290d6a8a0e8018&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5fc5e661d0f94cc23c0188b9bbe4e08&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8361af576f7e73b0bd2ea813976f60b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85ef35aaa38ac4f0c032c8bc3f6df559&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f15f59b3ff05825a61f252ed8f9a74e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b253411e54c35aa95f5f9179723bba3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd4cfbed43aa26af0eef694fecac2177&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25fb88c8ed14936954356d104de095d4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
