  <data key="d0">HDL Cholesterol</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">HDL cholesterol is known as "good" cholesterol, with low levels contributing to cardiovascular disease risk and being a diagnostic criterion of metabolic syndrome.&lt;SEP&gt;HDL Cholesterol is known as “good” cholesterol; raising its levels is considered beneficial for cardiovascular health, especially in patients with dyslipidaemia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8361af576f7e73b0bd2ea813976f60b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045</data>
