<node id="Micro-Vascular Complications">
  <data key="d0">Micro-Vascular Complications</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Micro-vascular complications are health issues that can arise from type 2 diabetes affecting small blood vessels, often already present in newly diagnosed patients.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578520</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Intensive Blood Glucose Control">
  <data key="d0">Intensive Blood Glucose Control</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Intensive blood glucose control is an approach designed to manage blood sugar levels in individuals with type 2 diabetes to prevent complications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578520</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hypertension">
  <data key="d0">Hypertension</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Hypertension refers to elevated blood pressure, which is a component of metabolic syndrome and increases cardiovascular risk.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypertension is a medical condition that can coexist with type 2 diabetes, affecting overall health and increasing the risk of cardiovascular disease.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypertension management involves various strategies for patients with diabetes to minimize health risks.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypertension is high blood pressure, which poses additional risks for patients with diabetes and is associated with nephropathy.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypertension is a medical condition often associated with diabetes that can worsen the risk of cardiovascular disease.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypertension is a condition characterized by elevated blood pressure, affecting kidney health and overall physiology.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1400e1158e4f7be2283a0366ebf4f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd4cfbed43aa26af0eef694fecac2177</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578520</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Screening for Type 2 Diabetes">
  <data key="d0">Screening for Type 2 Diabetes</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Screening for type 2 diabetes is a preventive measure recommended for high-risk groups to detect the condition early.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578520</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Insulin Therapy">
  <data key="d0">Insulin Therapy</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Insulin therapy is necessary for managing hyperglycemia in individuals with type 1 diabetes mellitus and may be applicable to some cases of type 2 diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578520</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Glycaemic Goals">
  <data key="d0">Glycaemic Goals</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Glycaemic goals refer to the target blood glucose levels established to minimize the risk of complications in diabetes management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578520</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="HbA1c">
  <data key="d0">HbA1c</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">HbA1c is a blood test providing an average level of blood sugar over the past 2 to 3 months, essential for diabetes management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578520</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fructosamine">
  <data key="d0">Fructosamine</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Fructosamine is a blood test that reflects average blood glucose levels over the previous 2-3 weeks, sometimes used in diabetes management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578520</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
