  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578520</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Polycystic Ovarian Syndrome">
  <data key="d0">Polycystic Ovarian Syndrome</data>
  <data key="d1">condition</data>
  <data key="d2">Polycystic ovarian syndrome is a hormonal disorder that is associated with insulin resistance and can occur in individuals with type 2 diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578520</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Acanthosis Nigricans">
  <data key="d0">Acanthosis Nigricans</data>
  <data key="d1">condition</data>
  <data key="d2">Acanthosis nigricans is a skin condition characterized by dark patches and is often associated with insulin resistance, which may occur in type 2 diabetes patients.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578520</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Individuals with Previous IFG or IGT">
  <data key="d0">Individuals with Previous IFG or IGT</data>
  <data key="d1">group</data>
  <data key="d2">Individuals previously diagnosed with impaired fasting glucose (IFG) or impaired glucose tolerance (IGT) are considered high-risk for developing type 2 diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578520</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ethnic Groups at High Risk">
  <data key="d0">Ethnic Groups at High Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">group</data>
  <data key="d2">Certain ethnic groups, including Pacific Islanders, Australian Aborigines, Mauritian, migrant Asian Indians, Chinese, Indigenous Americans, and Arabs, have elevated risk for type 2 diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578520</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cholesterol Absorption Inhibitor">
  <data key="d0">Cholesterol Absorption Inhibitor</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Cholesterol absorption inhibitors are a new class of cholesterol-lowering medications aimed at lowering LDL cholesterol, often used with statins.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578520</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Nicotinic Acid">
  <data key="d0">Nicotinic Acid</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Nicotinic acid is a medication used to manage diabetic dyslipidaemia and improve lipid profiles, despite its potential side effects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578520</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fibric Acids">
  <data key="d0">Fibric Acids</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Fibric acids, or fibrates, are medications considered as first-line therapy for patients with high triglycerides; they help manage lipid levels.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578520</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Omega-3 Fatty Acids">
  <data key="d0">Omega-3 Fatty Acids</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Omega-3 fatty acids, commonly derived from fish oil, play a significant role in managing high triglyceride levels and are often used in combination therapy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578521</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Combination Therapy">
  <data key="d0">Combination Therapy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Combination therapy refers to the use of multiple medications to manage dyslipidaemia and achieve desired lipid levels in patients with diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578521</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Aspirin Therapy">
  <data key="d0">Aspirin Therapy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Aspirin therapy is used as a secondary prevention method for cardiovascular disease in diabetic patients showing signs of cardiovascular issues.&lt;SEP&gt;Aspirin Therapy refers to the use of aspirin in prescribed doses for the prevention of cardiovascular disease in certain patient populations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578521</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cholestyramine">
  <data key="d0">Cholestyramine</data>
  <data key="d1">drug</data>
  <data key="d2">Cholestyramine is a bile acid sequestrant medication used in the treatment of high cholesterol, with a dose range of 4–16 g.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578521</data>
