<node id="Reye Syndrome">
  <data key="d0">Reye Syndrome</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Reye Syndrome is a rare but serious condition that causes swelling in the liver and brain, associated with aspirin use in children.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578522</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Glycaemic Control">
  <data key="d0">Glycaemic Control</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Glycaemic Control refers to the management of blood glucose levels in individuals with diabetes, aiming for target levels to prevent complications.&lt;SEP&gt;Glycaemic control refers to the management of blood glucose levels to prevent complications such as retinopathy and nephropathy in diabetic patients.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1400e1158e4f7be2283a0366ebf4f2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578522</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hypoglycaemia">
  <data key="d0">Hypoglycaemia</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Hypoglycaemia is a condition of abnormally low blood glucose levels often experienced by patients with diabetes, leading to various symptoms and potential complications.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypoglycaemia is a condition characterized by abnormally low blood glucose levels, often requiring education for recognition and management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578522</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sulfonylureas">
  <data key="d0">Sulfonylureas</data>
  <data key="d1">drug</data>
  <data key="d2">Sulfonylureas are a class of medications used to treat diabetes by stimulating insulin release from the pancreas.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578522</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Patients with Bleeding Tendency">
  <data key="d0">Patients with Bleeding Tendency</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Patients with Bleeding Tendency are individuals who cannot safely use aspirin due to the risk of increased bleeding.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578522</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Allergy">
  <data key="d0">Allergy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Allergy is a hypersensitive response by the immune system to substances that may cause adverse reactions, which can contraindicate aspirin use.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578523</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Active Hepatic Disease">
  <data key="d0">Active Hepatic Disease</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Active Hepatic Disease refers to current liver conditions that may contraindicate the use of aspirin due to potential complications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578523</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Recent Gastro-Intestinal Bleeding">
  <data key="d0">Recent Gastro-Intestinal Bleeding</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Recent Gastro-Intestinal Bleeding is a condition that can contraindicate the use of aspirin due to increased bleeding risks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578523</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="α-Glucosidase Inhibitors">
  <data key="d0">α-Glucosidase Inhibitors</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">α-Glucosidase inhibitors are medications used to delay carbohydrate absorption in diabetes management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578523</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Acarbose">
  <data key="d0">Acarbose</data>
  <data key="d1">drug</data>
  <data key="d2">Acarbose is a specific α-glucosidase inhibitor used at a dosage of 100–300 mg/day to delay carbohydrate absorption.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578523</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Miglitol">
  <data key="d0">Miglitol</data>
  <data key="d1">drug</data>
  <data key="d2">Miglitol is another α-glucosidase inhibitor that is also utilized to delay carbohydrate absorption at a dosage of 100–300 mg/day.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578523</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Short-acting Insulin">
  <data key="d0">Short-acting Insulin</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Short-acting insulin refers to insulins like regular and semilente that have an onset of action of 15–30 minutes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578524</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Intermediate-acting Insulin">
  <data key="d0">Intermediate-acting Insulin</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Intermediate-acting insulin such as NPH/lente has a longer onset time and is used to manage blood glucose over a more extended period.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578528</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Long-acting Insulin">
  <data key="d0">Long-acting Insulin</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Long-acting insulin like ultralente has an extended duration of action, providing stable blood glucose management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578528</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Insulin Analogs">
  <data key="d0">Insulin Analogs</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
