<node id="Logistic Regression">
  <data key="d0">Logistic Regression</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Logistic regression is a specific machine learning algorithm used for making predictions based on the correlation of various patient features.&lt;SEP&gt;Logistic regression is a statistical method used for binary classification that includes a logistic sigmoid function to model the probabilities of certain outcomes.&lt;SEP&gt;Logistic regression is a type of regression analysis used for binary classification tasks, fitting an S-shaped line to the data.&lt;SEP&gt;Logistic regression is a statistical method used to model the relationship between a dependent binary variable and one or more independent variables.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ec8cde6747414a42b9f90501d7dd0d2a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-010a987a088000cbaebd51b9889052f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-766aef888d040609f74bd8aa547e4350&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-189a42780d202026d1c3290c001f80ee</data>
