<node id="Artificial Neural Networks">
  <data key="d0">Artificial Neural Networks</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Artificial neural networks are computational models inspired by biological learning, used in deep learning to mimic brain function.&lt;SEP&gt;Artificial neural networks are computing systems inspired by biological neural networks that attempt to mimic the way human brains operate.&lt;SEP&gt;Artificial neural networks are a type of neural network designed for computational tasks, modeled after the learning processes of biological brains.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7030ceb5e481db7469c5a663054ab0ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e301584dbc493504e638dde9613d0a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95ce81b8a88d7af76b627732161bfd8d</data>
