<node id="Connectionism">
  <data key="d0">Connectionism</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Connectionism is an approach in cognitive science that relies on neural networks to understand intelligent behavior, associated with the second wave of deep learning development.&lt;SEP&gt;Connectionism is a theoretical approach to understanding the mind and brain that emphasizes interconnected neural units and emerged in neural network research.&lt;SEP&gt;Connectionism is a theoretical framework in cognitive science focused on understanding the mind through neural networks and their dynamics.&lt;SEP&gt;Connectionism is a theoretical framework in cognitive science focusing on how multiple interconnected units, like neurons, work together to create intelligent behavior.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7030ceb5e481db7469c5a663054ab0ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24b6e16206da653229333e2acff91797&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e301584dbc493504e638dde9613d0a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cd0905a2bbd4a2e98ea5834719f28254</data>
