<node id="Scalar">
  <data key="d0">Scalar</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A scalar is a single number used in linear algebra, typically represented by lower-case variable names in italics.&lt;SEP&gt;A scalar is a single numerical value that can be treated as a 1x1 matrix.&lt;SEP&gt;A scalar is a single numerical value that can represent the result of certain mathematical operations, including the dot product.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0d55b6724597822ab76201288059bd8f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d2e722934164a54c6a816c106572c75&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52465e8bb143dc190c7efa3f3e89fda6</data>
