<node id="Vector">
  <data key="d0">Vector</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A vector is an array of numbers arranged in order, identified by indices, and usually represented with lower case names in bold typeface.&lt;SEP&gt;A vector is a matrix with only one column, which can be represented as either a column or a row matrix.&lt;SEP&gt;A vector is a mathematical construct defining a direction and magnitude, used to describe the position in a space.&lt;SEP&gt;A Vector is a quantity defined by both a direction and a magnitude, commonly used in mathematics and physics.&lt;SEP&gt;A vector is a mathematical entity used in linear algebra, represented by an array of numbers, which can represent points in space.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0d55b6724597822ab76201288059bd8f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52465e8bb143dc190c7efa3f3e89fda6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0403607cb7181d4a13a232d13fec9630&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e325d64a50359748cfb47987a361fbb1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-88935c9c850ad773b6af22d7912a351e</data>
