<node id="Matrix Multiplication">
  <data key="d0">Matrix Multiplication</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Matrix multiplication is a method that involves combining two matrices to produce a third matrix under certain dimensional conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;Matrix multiplication is an operation that creates a new matrix from two matrices, provided that the number of columns in the first matrix matches the number of rows in the second.</data>
