  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Eigenvectors">
  <data key="d0">Eigenvectors</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Eigenvectors are non-zero vectors that change only in scale when multiplied by a corresponding matrix.&lt;SEP&gt;Eigenvectors are non-zero vectors that change at most by a scalar factor when a linear transformation is applied to them.&lt;SEP&gt;Eigenvectors are vectors that indicate the direction in which a transformation acts by stretching or compressing, associated with eigenvalue decomposition.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f81436ceefbaa6d5dc02610dd8127f9b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0139bf2dedbbf7d4064d9e8be650befc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0d3be7ce3dfb930212c12aac0c54ff0</data>
