<node id="Machine Learning">
  <data key="d0">Machine Learning</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Machine Learning is a subset of artificial intelligence (AI) characterized by its capability to extract patterns from raw data and make decisions based on that knowledge. It encompasses a variety of algorithms and models that enable systems to learn from data and enhance their performance over time. Machine Learning allows computer systems to improve through experience and data, signifying a shift from traditional programming to systems that learn dynamically.

The field focuses on the study of algorithms that empower machines to analyze data and generate predictions. This technique not only deals with data processing but also positions itself as a significant technology in various applications, including healthcare. In this domain, machine learning is utilized for predictive analytics and improving diagnostic accuracy, demonstrating its practical importance and versatility.

Machine Learning fundamentally involves the use of computers and algorithms to process vast amounts of data, identifying patterns without the need for explicit programming. This capacity to learn from experience and enhance algorithms over time distinguishes it as a pivotal aspect of modern AI, revolutionizing how systems interact with and understand data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-010a987a088000cbaebd51b9889052f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2aff4303e41c5babfaf2c4d7bf68299d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bac272cb401529a36c7732284f3da738&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd2a057016fddbfc53fb1a5ab4973351&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d052846d3bce5d76b5380e3fe4a4925e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4efb878cf5f2d0b22579e2bf5668edd1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5d27c2834816e4173fcae098e70bc6a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-189a42780d202026d1c3290c001f80ee</data>
