  <data key="d2">Matrix Inversion is a mathematical method used to find the inverse of a matrix, essential for solving linear equations.&lt;SEP&gt;Matrix inversion refers to finding an inverse of a matrix which is not defined for non-square matrices and involves unique mappings for solutions.</data>
