  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The pseudoinverse is a matrix computation used to provide solutions for linear equations, especially in cases of underdetermined or overdetermined systems.&lt;SEP&gt;The pseudoinverse allows for general solutions to linear equations when the conditions of square matrices for inversion are not met.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0139bf2dedbbf7d4064d9e8be650befc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-443f6360d2d3fc61bef3f5a8c109e2f2</data>
