<node id="Equation">
  <data key="d0">Equation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The equation discussed pertains to the determination of solutions based on linear combinations and vector spaces.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-88935c9c850ad773b6af22d7912a351e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578897</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Column Space">
  <data key="d0">Column Space</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The column space refers to the span of the columns of a matrix in linear algebra, determining the possible solutions to an equation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-88935c9c850ad773b6af22d7912a351e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578897</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="R">
  <data key="d0">R</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">R denotes the set of real numbers and is a common notation in mathematics used to represent numerical values.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-88935c9c850ad773b6af22d7912a351e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578897</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Linear Combination">
  <data key="d0">Linear Combination</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A linear combination involves the summation of multiple vectors, each multiplied by corresponding scalar coefficients.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-88935c9c850ad773b6af22d7912a351e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578897</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dimension">
  <data key="d0">Dimension</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Dimension refers to the number of independent directions in a space, determining the complexity of a vector or matrix.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-88935c9c850ad773b6af22d7912a351e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578897</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Linearly Independent Columns">
  <data key="d0">Linearly Independent Columns</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Linearly independent columns in a matrix imply that no column can be formed as a linear combination of the others, crucial for unique solutions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-88935c9c850ad773b6af22d7912a351e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769578897</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
