<node id="IoMT">
  <data key="d0">IoMT</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Internet of Medical Things (IoMT) refers to the interconnected network of medical devices that collect and share health data, improving diagnosis and treatment in healthcare.&lt;SEP&gt;The Internet of Medical Things (IoMT) refers to a network of connected medical devices that enhance healthcare delivery and monitoring.&lt;SEP&gt;The Internet of Medical Things (IoMT) refers to connected medical devices and applications that communicate over the internet for healthcare tasks.&lt;SEP&gt;The Internet of Medical Things (IoMT) refers to interconnected medical devices that collect and transmit health data.&lt;SEP&gt;IoMT stands for the Internet of Medical Things, representing a network of connected medical devices that can collect and share data.&lt;SEP&gt;IoMT refers to the Internet of Medical Things, encompassing connected medical devices and their integration into healthcare systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11a8a4925599d83f5b5063a2bdbd9aa6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0022476db89861fe923b166435aa071d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0b5b0dada3f2da060cb36b4d5f30503c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe9d12fa571571f61c1ced09ffa9e288&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-26bbc9a627a1f70c00a8266b945934c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5d27c2834816e4173fcae098e70bc6a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a068e5b419a16a4c176cbf29b84904c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-daee1cca01fc2eaa59c3871509e41246</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769582103</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="MQTT">
  <data key="d0">MQTT</data>
  <data key="d1">protocol</data>
  <data key="d2">MQTT is an asynchronous messaging protocol that connects embedded systems to middleware and applications, suitable for resource-constrained devices and low-bandwidth networks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11a8a4925599d83f5b5063a2bdbd9aa6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769582103</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CoAP">
  <data key="d0">CoAP</data>
  <data key="d1">protocol</data>
  <data key="d2">CoAP is a web transfer protocol designed for devices with limited processing power, implemented in IoT communications sensitive to traffic congestion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11a8a4925599d83f5b5063a2bdbd9aa6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769582103</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="XMPP">
  <data key="d0">XMPP</data>
  <data key="d1">protocol</data>
  <data key="d2">XMPP is a messaging protocol based on IETF standards, mainly used for sending and receiving messages with a publish/subscribe mechanism.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11a8a4925599d83f5b5063a2bdbd9aa6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769582103</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AMQP">
  <data key="d0">AMQP</data>
  <data key="d1">protocol</data>
  <data key="d2">AMQP is a messaging protocol designed for business applications, ensuring message orientation, switching, and reliability.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11a8a4925599d83f5b5063a2bdbd9aa6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769582103</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Low-Power Wireless Personal Area Networks (LoWPANs)">
  <data key="d0">Low-Power Wireless Personal Area Networks (LoWPANs)</data>
  <data key="d1">network</data>
  <data key="d2">LoWPANs extend the RST architecture to low-power devices, facilitating communication in IoT applications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11a8a4925599d83f5b5063a2bdbd9aa6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769582103</data>
