<node id="CT Scan">
  <data key="d0">CT Scan</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">CT scan is a medical imaging technique that allows healthcare professionals to diagnose diseases in a painless and non-invasive manner.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9c9a45da562d9c6c7d3cc26d1b4aa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769582103</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Magnetic Resonance Imaging">
  <data key="d0">Magnetic Resonance Imaging</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Magnetic Resonance Imaging is a medical imaging technique used to visualize internal structures of the body.&lt;SEP&gt;Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) uses magnetic fields and radio waves to produce detailed body images noninvasively.&lt;SEP&gt;Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) is a non-invasive imaging technique that produces comprehensive three-dimensional images using a high magnetic field and radio waves.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9c9a45da562d9c6c7d3cc26d1b4aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a7bad11e7fd573eedc2ce2521ce1b37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-daee1cca01fc2eaa59c3871509e41246</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769582103</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="X-ray">
  <data key="d0">X-ray</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">X-ray is a painless imaging test that generates images of the body's interior components, particularly bones, using small amounts of radiation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9c9a45da562d9c6c7d3cc26d1b4aa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769582103</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ultrasound">
  <data key="d0">Ultrasound</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Ultrasound is an imaging technique that uses sound waves to create pictures of organs, tissues, and structures inside the body, without employing radiation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9c9a45da562d9c6c7d3cc26d1b4aa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769582103</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Internet of Medical Things">
  <data key="d0">Internet of Medical Things</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Internet of Medical Things (IoMT) refers to connected medical devices and technology that enhance patient care and safety.&lt;SEP&gt;The Internet of Medical Things is a network of medical devices and applications that communicate with healthcare IT systems.&lt;SEP&gt;The Internet of Medical Things is a subset of IoT focused on the health sector, connecting medical devices to the internet.&lt;SEP&gt;Internet of Medical Things (IoMT) refers to the network of medical devices and applications that connect to healthcare IT systems through online computer networks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9c9a45da562d9c6c7d3cc26d1b4aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81ed5407d536198f9d377925116fc2f8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-daee1cca01fc2eaa59c3871509e41246&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-378b4d849b71c1f82db0e448abf78101</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769582103</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Wireless Sensor Networks">
  <data key="d0">Wireless Sensor Networks</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Wireless Sensor Networks are networks of spatially distributed autonomous sensors that monitor physical or environmental conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;Wireless Sensor Networks (WSNs) are networks composed of distributed sensor nodes that collect and transmit data, often requiring specific management for energy and data flow.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9c9a45da562d9c6c7d3cc26d1b4aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-daee1cca01fc2eaa59c3871509e41246</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769582104</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="IEEE 802.15.4">
  <data key="d0">IEEE 802.15.4</data>
  <data key="d1">standard</data>
  <data key="d2">IEEE 802.15.4 is a low-cost, low-power networking standard primarily for low-bandwidth IoT devices, defining physical and media access control layers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9c9a45da562d9c6c7d3cc26d1b4aa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769582104</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="IoMT Communication Protocols">
  <data key="d0">IoMT Communication Protocols</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">IoMT communication protocols are sets of rules enabling data transmission for the Internet of Medical Things, categorized based on the five-layered IoMT architecture.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9c9a45da562d9c6c7d3cc26d1b4aa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769582104</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Perception Layer Protocols">
  <data key="d0">Perception Layer Protocols</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Perception layer protocols refer to the communication standards that manage data collection and transmission in IoMT applications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9c9a45da562d9c6c7d3cc26d1b4aa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1769582104</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Network Layer Protocols">
  <data key="d0">Network Layer Protocols</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Network layer protocols are responsible for the routing and delivery of data packets in IoMT systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9c9a45da562d9c6c7d3cc26d1b4aa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
